rpetual cloud cover, beckons intrepid explorers with its otherworldly beauty and intriguing mysteries. Ishtar Terra boasts colossal mountain ranges, where peaks thrust defiantly through thick sulfuric clouds, casting surreal shadows on the barren surface below. The terrain, punctuated by vast lava plains and jagged ridges, presents a landscape both haunting and captivating. Among its geological wonders, the Maxwell Montes reigns supreme, soaring to heights unmatched elsewhere in the solar system. These towering peaks provide a stunning vantage point to witness Venus\'s swirling atmosphere and fierce winds, while its lower valleys cradle labyrinthine riverbeds etched by eons of relentless weathering.','Ishtar Terra',15,1,16,1,'Sightseeing the majestic storms, marveling at the mesmerizing cloud formations, capturing breathtaking photos of the turbulent atmosphere, experiencing the thrill of witnessing atmospheric drama, and feeling the awe of standing in the midst of cosmic spectacle.','Sky diving, Para Gliding','Whirlwind, turbulent, tempestuous, tumultuous, chaotic, unpredictable, fierce, cyclonic, raging, tumultuous, turbulent, atmospheric mayhem.','Great aurora, solar eclipse'),(26,3,4.5,3200000000,'Aphrodite Terra, situated on the scorching surface of Venus, is a mesmerizing expanse of highlands that beckon exploration. This captivating region is named after the Greek goddess of love and beauty, fittingly, as its rugged beauty is otherworldly. As you journey through Aphrodite Terra, you\'ll be awestruck by its dramatic contrasts. Aphrodite Terra is a geological enigma, with its origins still not fully understood. Volcanic activity, tectonic forces, and extreme temperatures have sculpted this surreal landscape. The scorching temperatures, corrosive atmosphere, and crushing pressure make it a harsh environment for exploration, but robotic missions have ventured here, providing invaluable insights into Venus\'s mysterious past.','Aphrodite Terra',9,1,13,2,'Sightseei