INSERT INTO `planets` VALUES (1,'Jupiter',629,'Behold the majestic giant of our solar system - Jupiter! This gas giant is a captivating sight with its iconic Great Red Spot and numerous swirling storms. Marvel at its vast size, which could fit more than 1,300 Earths inside. Dive into the mysteries of Jupiter\'s turbulent atmosphere and learn about its many moons, including the fascinating Europa, which hides a subsurface ocean. Join us for a cosmic adventure around the largest planet in our solar system.',95,5.6,'2024-09-12'),(2,'Mercury',92,'Welcome to the closest planet to the Sun! Mercury, named after the Roman god of speed, lives up to its name as the fastest planet in our solar system. Its surface is a stark contrast - scorching during the day and freezing at night due to its lack of atmosphere to retain heat. Explore its rugged terrain, ancient impact craters, and unique rocky landscape on a space adventure like no other.',0,1.5,'2024-03-25'),(3,'Venus',41,'Journey to Earth?s \"sister planet,\" Venus, where you\'ll witness the beauty of its thick atmosphere and swirling clouds. Despite its serene appearance, Venus is a hostile world with extreme temperatures, making it the hottest planet in our solar system. Marvel at its mysterious features, including vast volcanoes and massive canyons, as you embark on a once-in-a-lifetime space odyssey.',0,1.1,'2024-01-14'),(4,'Mars',78,'Prepare for an exciting Martian adventure! Mars, often called the Red Planet, is a captivating destination with its rusty surface and intriguing geological formations. Explore its canyons, valleys, and polar ice caps. Learn about the ongoing exploration efforts to unravel the mysteries of Mars and the possibility of human colonization in the future. Get ready to experience the allure of the fourth planet from the Sun.',2,0.9,'2023-12-10'),(5,'Saturn',1275,'Prepare to be mesmerized by Saturn, the ringed wonder of our solar system! Saturn\'s stunning ring system is a sight to behold, composed of icy particles and rocky debris. Explore the intricate patterns of its rings and admire the beauty of its multiple moons, including the remarkable Titan. Delve into the scientific wonders of this gas giant while enjoying the breathtaking views that make Saturn a jewel in the night sky.',146,6.0,'2025-05-01'),(6,'Uranus',2721,'Embark on a unique journey to Uranus, the quirky planet that rolls on its side as it orbits the Sun. This ice giant is known for its peculiar rotational axis, giving it a distinct appearance in our solar system. Explore its chilly atmosphere, icy rings, and fascinating moons. Discover the secrets of Uranus\'s unique tilt and how it influences its magnetic field, making it a captivating destination for space enthusiasts.',27,10.4,'2026-08-11'),(7,'Neptune',4352,'Dive into the depths of the outer solar system and explore Neptune, the blue giant planet. Named after the god of the sea, Neptune\'s vibrant blue hue is a result of methane in its atmosphere. Witness the powerful storms and winds that sweep across its surface and marvel at the majestic Great Dark Spot. Learn about its diverse moon system, including Triton, a moon with geysers and icy plains. Join us on a celestial voyage to this distant and mysterious planet.',14,11.1,'2027-02-17'),(8,'Earth',0,'Discover the wonders of the only known planet to support life - Earth! Experience the breathtaking beauty of diverse landscapes, from vast oceans to towering mountains. Witness the harmony of nature and human civilization, and learn about the unique ecosystems that make our planet a haven for life. Join us on a space tour to appreciate the delicate balance that sustains life on Earth.',1,NULL,NULL);
